     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickScramblingCircuit[a, spec, ...] generate the Wick circuit (i.e., \
quantum circuits of fermionic Gaussian gates) realization of a(t) := \
u^\\[Dagger] (t) a u(t) for the study quantum information scrambling, where a \
is a local Wick unitary operator and u(t) is the time-evolution operator. For \
the remaining arguments spec, ..., see RandomWickCircuit. \
WickScramblingCircuit[k, spec, ...] assumes a := exp[\\[Pi]/2 ( \
f_k^\\[Dagger] f k + 1 - f_k + 1^\\[Dagger] fk)] on the k^th and (k + 1) th \
fermion modes.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "WickScramblingCircuit", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "WickScramblingCircuit", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/WickScramblingCircuit"}},
